Africa
------
[1] Guinea-Bissau
Date: Fri 20 Mar 2015
Source: StarAfrica, African Press Agency (APA) report [edited]
http://en.starafrica.com/news/gbissau-records-12-measles-cases-official.html


Guinea Bissau has been hit by the highly contagious infection measles disease as 12 out of 29 suspected cases appeared positive after a test, the Minister of the Public Health Service (Valentina Mendes) confirmed [Thu 19 Mar 2015]. Appealing for general mobilization, the health official has urged the general populations to abide by the instructions of the health professionals and asked parents to take their children who show signs of the disease to the closest health facilities in a bid to ensure early diagnosis and adequate treatment.

The suspected cases whose blood showed measles symptoms come from Bafata eastern region (7 cases), Tombali in the South (2 cases), Cacheu up North (1 case), and Bissau, the capital (2 cases).

