[5] Papua New Guinea and Vanuatu (WHO)
Date: Sun 15 Mar 2015
Source: WHO, Western Pacific Region, Programmes and projects Combating communicable diseases [edited]
http://www.wpro.who.int/southpacific/programmes/communicable_diseases/disease_surveillance_response/PSS-15-March-2015/en/


There are measles outbreaks ongoing in Papua New Guinea and Vanuatu.

A measles immunization campaign continues in Port Vila and Efate province, Vanuatu following the Tropical Cyclone Pam [6 Mar 2015].

